div.p:
When the Savior came among the Nephites after his resurrection in Palestine, he taught these
early Americans a most important lesson on this point. Said he: ". . . there shall be no
disputations among you, as there have hitherto been;

"Behold, this is not my doctrine, to stir up the hearts of men with anger, one against another;
but this is my doctrine, that such things should be done away"
(3 Ne. 11:28-30).
